Sentencas: Mixed ionic and electronic conductor SmBa(0.5)Sr(0.5)CocuO(5+delta) (SBSCCo) is studied as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Characterization of SmBa0.5Sr0.5CoCuO5+δ cathode based on GDC and LSGM electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction spectra show that SBSCCo are chemical compatible with Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 (GDC) and La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.83Mg0.17O2.865 (LSGM) electrolyte below 950 degrees C. XPS analysis results indicate that the transition-metal cations on the SBSCCo sample's surface exhibit two different valence state, i.e. Co3+/Co4+ and Cu2+/Cu+.
Titulo: Characterization of SmBa0.5Sr0.5CoCuO5+δ cathode based on GDC and LSGM electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The average thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) of SBSCCo cathode is 16.14 x 10(-6) K-1 between 30 degrees C and 850 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Characterization of SmBa0.5Sr0.5CoCuO5+δ cathode based on GDC and LSGM electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of SBSCCo cathode reaches 110-206 Scm(-1) between 200 degrees C and 850 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Characterization of SmBa0.5Sr0.5CoCuO5+δ cathode based on GDC and LSGM electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area specific resistances of SBSCCo cathode on LSGM and GDC electrolytes are 0.0263 and 0.0274 Omega cm(2) at 850 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Characterization of SmBa0.5Sr0.5CoCuO5+δ cathode based on GDC and LSGM electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum output power density of a single cell with SBSCCo cathode on LSGM and GDC electrolyte reaches 857 and 633 mWcm(-2)
Titulo: Characterization of SmBa0.5Sr0.5CoCuO5+δ cathode based on GDC and LSGM electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
Characterization of SmBa0.5Sr0.5CoCuO5+δ cathode based on GDC and LSGM electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance of SBSCCo cathode based on LSGM electrolyte is better than on GDC electrolyte.
Titulo: Characterization of SmBa0.5Sr0.5CoCuO5+δ cathode based on GDC and LSGM electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These primarily results indicate that SBSCCo is a candidate cathode material for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Characterization of SmBa0.5Sr0.5CoCuO5+δ cathode based on GDC and LSGM electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
